      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "The documentation is hidden for bitcoind.\r\n\r\nsudo bitcoind -h | grep dbbatchsize\r\n\r\nI also suggested the default value is problematic.\r\n\r\n> Initial block download is slower and more problematic without this setting due to download batches exceeding the dbbatchsize.\r\n\r\n> Multiple connections are factored into batch size estimates, so it seems the optimal default setting is ((16 << 20) * 8) to avoid erroneously clearing batches here:\r\n\r\n> https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/txdb.cpp#L143\r\n\r\nWould it be wrong to document this as the recommended dbbatchsize value during initial block download?\r\n\r\nInitial block download took about 4 days with no issues using less than the minimum required spec.",
